body:
interesting. we haven't encountered issues with specific .NET versions.
the error suggests the env with default logger wasn't created successfully.
maybe you can try debug further with the suggestion in https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/8545#issuecomment-1082451066

@chilo-ms , any ideas? have you had any issues with .NET 6 ?
You could try explictly creating the environment by calling OrtEnv.Instance(). You don't need to do anything with the return value.

@jywu-msft @skottmckay Thank you so much for your input! I was able to resolve the issue with the information that you guys provided.

Calling `OrtEnv.Instance()` allowed me to bypass the issue of initializing the environment with the default logger and then initializing the `InferenceSession` threw another exception about failing to load "onnxruntime_providers_tensorrt.dll" library. However, it pointed to the DLL that resides in "bin\Debug\net6.0\runtimes\win-x64\native" path instead of the DLL in the  application output directory "bin\Debug\net6.0". Copying TensorRT DLLs to the former path solved the issue and now everything works fine as intended.

.NET framework doesn't have the same output directory structure as .NET 6 so it had everything thrown together into the "bin/Debug" output directory and it seems this is why I didn't have this issue there. 

Again, thank you both for your help. Issue is now resolved!

Glad to hear your issue is resolved!
On our side, we need to find a better way to surface warning message about the missing/incorrect dependency.
As you might have noticed in the other issues I pointed to. the DefaultLogger error message is usually an indication of a missing dependency, but in your original comment it sounded like you had the correct dependencies. (but it turns out .net6.0 looks for them in a different location)

Exactly. This is my first time trying TensorRT EP in a .NET 6 app and it was kinda confusing why it didn't work even though the dlls were there. Initializing ORT environment explicitly got me the correct error message along with the path of the failing DLL so this seems to be a great debugging workaround until more informative error messages are used!

issue.title: Create OrtEnv earlier in C# code

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 
Trigger creation of OrtEnv in the C# SessionOptions constructor so that the default logger is available if any calls to NativeMethods made by SessionOptions fail internally.

Currently we do this in the C# InferenceSession class, but that is too late for any errors that come from adding EPs to the session options.

**Motivation and Context**
#11572
